  <text xml:lang="la">
    <body>
      <p xml:id="ANOFRAG_MOBB8420001"><pb n="[f.77v]"/>Isidora. Musica est ars modulandi sono cantuque consistens</p>
      <p xml:id="ANOFRAG_MOBB8420002">proporcio bis diapason est proporcio quadrupla</p>
      <p xml:id="ANOFRAG_MOBB8420003">proporcio diapason in proporcio dupla</p>
      <p xml:id="ANOFRAG_MOBB8420004">diastema optusa rectangula</p>
      <p xml:id="ANOFRAG_MOBB8420005">dismutacio est mutacio a [uno add. supra lin.] modo. ad modum alterum vel a colore ad alium colorem</p>
      <p xml:id="ANOFRAG_MOBB8420006">de minimis non curat lex</p>
      <p xml:id="ANOFRAG_MOBB8420007">alteracio in musica est transposicio in figura causa carentis numero</p>
      <p xml:id="ANOFRAG_MOBB8420008">Numerus sexdecim. est numerus perfectissimus. quia semper potest dividi in duas partes equales. ut 16. ad 8. vel 8. ad 4. vel 4 ad duo</p>
      <p xml:id="ANOFRAG_MOBB8420009">Tonus dicitur ex duobus semitonijs inequalibus. scilicet ex semitono maiore. et semitono minore</p>
      <p xml:id="ANOFRAG_MOBB8420010"><pb n="[f.78r]"/>Pobasapanegius. Perdiabolite. diatriphon. epithesituastrofo pegliceron. Ci.anonexapereon. meloneptabile Pasafostios [ras.] Fonealoge</p>
      <p xml:id="ANOFRAG_MOBB8420011">[Oxford, Bodleian Library, Bodley 842, f.78r,1; text: Proporciones, 6, 8, 9, 12, tonus, diatessaron, diapente, diapason, sesquialtra 6.4, sesquialtra 3.2, sesquitercia 4.3, sesquitercia 8.6, sesquioctava .98. dupla proporcio et dicitur 4.2] 
      <figure><graphic url="/images/ANOFRAG_01GF.gif"/></figure></p>
      <p xml:id="ANOFRAG_MOBB8420012">Et nota quod iste quatuor tales</p>
      <p xml:id="ANOFRAG_MOBB8420013">[Oxford, Bodleian Library, Bodley 842, f.78r,2]</p>
      <p xml:id="ANOFRAG_MOBB8420014">valent istas quatuor tales</p>
      <p xml:id="ANOFRAG_MOBB8420015">[Oxford, Bodleian Library, Bodley 842, f.78r,3]</p>
      <p xml:id="ANOFRAG_MOBB8420016">et sic infini sunt proporciones</p>
    </body>
